{
    "id": "3dprinting/blob-of-death",
    "title": "Witness a Blob of Death",
    "description": "Skipping a first-layer check lets a failed Z homing extrude in mid-air, engulfing the nozzle in molten plastic.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/blob_of_death_nozzle_fail.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/sydney.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Sydney here. You skip the first-layer check, the Z axis mis-homes, and molten PLA begins wrapping the hotend. Goggles on, stay clear of moving axes, and keep a fire extinguisher within reach.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "3dprint-blob-of-death",
                    "text": "Let it run and document the failure."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "cooldown",
                    "text": "Kill power, let the blob cool, and list the damage.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "8896a0ef-edd8-4d19-ac14-19ee66470e54",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "cooldown",
            "text": "Unplug the printer, wait for the hotend to reach room temp, then move the gantry by hand to confirm it's free. Lay out goggles, pliers, a spare nozzle, and paper towels.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "repair-blob-of-death",
                    "text": "Peel away plastic, swap the nozzle, and re-seat wiring."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify",
                    "text": "Printer cleaned and reassembled.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "8aa6dc27-dc42-4622-ac88-cbd57f48625f",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "verify",
            "text": "Run a controlled first-layer test and log the outcome. Pass only if adhesion is even and no fresh ooze wraps the nozzle in the first minute.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Verification pass is clean and repair notes are logged.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "8aa6dc27-dc42-4622-ac88-cbd57f48625f",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "60409c3f-56cf-4b9e-9e60-ca480d4896d0",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "contamination",
                    "text": "Fresh ooze or smoke appears during verification.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "8aa6dc27-dc42-4622-ac88-cbd57f48625f",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "contamination",
            "text": "Troubleshooting branch: stop immediately, cool down, inspect heater block insulation, and clean residual filament before retrying. If wiring looks damaged, halt and replace components before power-on.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "cooldown",
                    "text": "Safe to retry teardown and rebuild.",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "8aa6dc27-dc42-4622-ac88-cbd57f48625f",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Blob removed, nozzle stable, and verification logged. Next time, stay for the first layer, check Z offset, and keep the bed clean so you don't repeat the mess.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Lesson learned."
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "rewards": [
        {
            "id": "fe46e236-5d03-4c95-9b38-68b045a0df03",
            "count": 1
        }
    ],
    "requiresQuests": [
        "3dprinting/nozzle-cleaning"
    ],
